17/09/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- US Undersecretary of State for Political Affairs Nicholas Burns called on Turkey to play a proactive role in the Middle East, Turkish media reported on Saturday (September 15th).
"The Turkish people have just concluded important, even historic elections," Burns said, speaking at the Atlantic Council in Washington on Thursday.
He added that with these elections, a new period has begun in relations between Turkey and the United States.
Turkey is the most influential democracy in the Muslim world, Burns said.
He described President Abdullah Gul and Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan as reliable people who can be trusted.
(Hurriyet - 17/09/07;
CNN Turk, Zaman - 15/09/07)
